[normal]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Q1 [bold]Is cycling safe, particularly in towns and cities?[bold]&#xa0;[bold]1.
[normal] 
[normal] 
[normal]This is a matter of perception. 
[normal]Aviva recognises that 
[normal]a great deal of 
[normal]Government 
[normal]resource
[normal] has
[normal] 
[normal]already 
[normal]been invested
[normal] and this has undoubtedly resulted in 
[normal]the 
[normal]advancement 
[normal]of
[normal] 
[normal]cycling 
[normal]safety
[normal]. However
[normal],
[normal] comparisons with other countries suggest there is still considerable scope for further improvement in the UK.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Q2 [bold]What could central and local government do to improve cycling safety?[bold]&#xa0;[bold]2.
[normal] 
[normal] 
[normal]T
[normal]here have been many debates and consultations on such matters and so Aviva will restrict comment to the following points, where 
[normal]it is felt 
[normal]we can add 
[normal]useful 
[normal]insight
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.
[normal] 
[normal] 
[normal]In 
[normal]Aviva’s e
[normal]xperience, most 
[normal]serious 
[normal]collisions between a motorist and a cyclist involve the driver simply not seeing the cyclist before impact.
[normal] They tend to occur at junctions and roundabouts
[normal]. R
[normal]arely is the driver blatantly reckless and invariably they are mo
[normal]rtified by what has happened. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4. 
[normal] 
[normal]Aviva believes that 
[normal]to effectively tackle this type of 
[normal]occurrence
[normal], the issues and consequences need to be 
[normal]embedded in the public psyche
[normal] and that this
[normal] 
[normal]is 
[normal]p
[normal]robably
[normal] best 
[normal]achieved by 
[normal]raising awareness via 
[normal]a 
[normal]‘
[normal]hard hitting
[normal]’
[normal] 
[normal]communication campaign
[normal]. Certainly this should utilise 
[normal]TV 
[normal]and printed 
[normal]advert
[normal]ising
[normal], but also 
[normal]other 
[normal]forms of 
[normal]social media
[normal]. The adverts should aim to have a 
[normal]similar 
[normal]gravitas 
[normal]to those previously used 
[normal]to encourage seat belt usage and to 
[normal]look twice for
[normal] oncoming 
[normal]m
[normal]otorcyclist
[normal]s
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]Whilst commendable, the current 
[normal]THINK
[normal]!
[normal] ‘Look Out’ 
[normal]for 
[normal]cyclists’
[normal] 
[normal]campaign 
[normal]does not seem to have 
[normal]a great deal of 
[normal]supporting video, nor has 
[normal]it 
[normal]achieved 
[normal]sufficient
[normal]ly high
[normal] profile yet.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5. 
[normal] A
[normal] nationwide advert would provide an opportunity to demonstrate benefits 
[normal]such as
[normal] cyclists 
[normal]w
[normal]earing a helmet / hi-viz clothing
[normal],
[normal] warn about the dangers of under-taking / use of ear phones and promote the availability of any free / low cost cycling training sch
[normal]emes (themes preferably to be agreed in advance with recognised cycling associations such as the CTC
[normal] &amp; LCC
[normal]). 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]6. 
[normal] 
[normal]Specifically in relation to collisions 
[normal]involving 
[normal]LGVs / Construction Vehicles turning left at a junction
[normal],
[normal] 
[normal]Aviva is supportive of the recently
[normal] produced Construction Logistics Standard, which we feel represents good practice and would encourage operators / clients to 
[normal]build 
[normal]this 
[normal]into the
[normal]ir
[normal] procurement process
[normal]. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]7. 
[normal] 
[normal]T
[normal]ransport for London
[normal]’s 
[normal]Fleet Operator Recognition Scheme
[normal] (FORS)
[normal] 
[normal]is 
[normal]another 
[normal]excellent 
[normal]initiative
[normal], of
[normal] 
[normal]which 
[normal]Aviva 
[normal]is supportive
[normal],
[normal] and 
[normal]it is felt 
[normal]should be 
[normal]publicised and 
[normal]extended to other regions as quickly as possible.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]8. 
[normal] 
[normal]Aviva currently
[normal] offer
[normal]s
[normal] to
[normal] 
[normal]fund the cost of supplying 
[normal]our Fleet LGV customers 
[normal]with warning decals (
[normal]illustrated 
[normal]below)
[normal] and Fresnel lenses
[normal]. We
[normal] consider 
[normal]this 
[normal]to be a cost effective means to raise 
[normal]both 
[normal]cyclist awareness and 
[normal]to 
[normal]improve the driver’s field of vision respectively. This initiative has received widespread 
[normal]praise
[normal] and 
[normal]Government might 
[normal]like to 
[normal]consi
[normal]der 
[normal]making the dist
[normal]inctive
[normal] 
[normal]/
[normal] intuitive
[normal] decal 
[normal]in particular
