[normal] FORS
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]9. 
[normal]  
[normal]Aviva is of the view that all professional drivers should 
[normal]complete a Vulnerable Road User focused module as part of their mandatory Driver CPC training, preferably 
[normal]to include physically experiencing things from 
[normal]the perspective of a cyclist.
[normal]   
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Q3 [bold]Is it desirable and feasible to segregate cyclists from other road[bold] users, for example by [bold]prohibiting HGVs from entering city centres at peak hours?[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]10
[normal]. 
[normal] 
[normal]Following a 
[normal]review of 
[normal]killed and 
[normal]serious
[normal]ly
[normal] injur
[normal]ed
[normal] cyclist
[normal] 
[normal]claims 
[normal]on
[normal] our Commercial Motor account, Aviva is 
[normal]believes
[normal] that the most effective means to protect cyclists is to 
[normal]physically
[normal] separate 
[normal]them from other road 
[normal]users.
[normal] Wherever this is possible, 
[normal]such
[normal] segregation will also substantially remove the sources of antagonism that otherwise inevitably arise between the two fa
[normal]ctions.  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]11. 
[normal]In London at least, Police data confirms that most incidents involving cyclists occur during peak commuter times. With this in mind, Aviva believes there is justification to at least explore the prospect of 
[normal]restricting access to certain road
[normal] networks for
[normal] some vehicles 
[normal]during
[normal] certain times
[normal] of the day
[normal]. The matter is of course complicated by the number of different stakeholders involved and the risk of unintended 
[normal]consequences
[normal]. Perhaps there is scope to undertake a limited trial &amp;/or introduce me
[normal]asures only for vehicles which do not meet stipulated safety standards as a means to encourage greater compliance.
